<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc9e322fe-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s455a"><num value="455a">§ 455a.</num><heading> State taxation; lands of desert-land entryman</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The lands of any desert-land entryman located within an irrigation project constructed under the Reclamation Act and obtaining a water supply from such project, and for whose land water has been actually available for a period of four years, may likewise be taxed by the State or political subdivision thereof in which such lands are located.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc9e322ff-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/act/1928-04-21/ch394/s2">Apr. 21, 1928, ch. 394, § 2</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/45/439">45 Stat. 439</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1930-06-13/ch477">June 13, 1930, ch. 477</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/46/581">46 Stat. 581</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idc9e32300-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idc9e32301-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
